agent_scope_database.name: Introduction
agent_scope_database.content: Launch Agent 6 is an Agent focused on building credit infrastructure for permissionless finance, with a focus on the Plasma ecosystem. Launch Agent 6 serves as a neutral platform enabling stablecoin distribution hubs—including exchanges, wallets, and neobanks—to access institutional-grade lending infrastructure underpinning USDS, sUSDS and other Sky benefits. With a focus on USDT, Launch Agent 6 acts as the central liquidity hub catalyzing the expansion of USDT-denominated assets across DeFi and OTC lending markets, RWAs, and PayFi within Sky’s collateral portfolio. Launch Agent 6 provides USDT holders with access to the Sky Savings Rate within its own suite of B2B2C and B2C savings products.

agent_scope_database.name: Routine Protocol
agent_scope_database.content: The documents herein define the process for using the Root Edit Primitive to update the Launch Agent 6 Agent Artifact in routine or normal conditions (i.e., non-emergency situations).

agent_scope_database.name: Root Edit Proposal Submission
agent_scope_database.content: The Root Edit process begins with an AGENT6 token holder submitting a proposal through the Powerhouse system containing a draft Artifact Edit Proposal. An AGENT6 token holder must hold at least 1% of the circulating token supply to submit a proposal. The proposal must also be posted on the Sky Forum under the “Launch Agent 6 Prime” category.

agent_scope_database.name: Short-Term Transitionary Measures
agent_scope_database.content: Until the Powerhouse system supports submitting Artifact Edit Proposals, AGENT6 token holders may submit Artifact Edit Proposals by posting them to the Sky Forum under the “Launch Agent 6 Prime” category. The title of the post must include the text “Launch Agent 6 Artifact Edit Proposal”. The post must include cryptographic proof that the author controls an account holding the required percentage of the total Launch Agent 6 token supply specified in [**Root Edit Proposal Submission** _(Core)_ - The Root Edit process begins with an AGENT6 token holder submitting a proposal through the Powerhouse system containing a draft Artifact Edit Proposal. An AGENT6 token holder must hold at least 1% of the circulating token supply to submit a proposal. The proposal must also be posted on the Sky Forum under the “Launch Agent 6 Prime” category.](https://www.notion.so/Root-Edit-Proposal-Submission-Core-The-Root-Edit-process-begins-with-an-AGENT6-token-holder-subm-2b6f2ff08d7381d49962e9bd41a6f0e1?pvs=21).

agent_scope_database.name: Root Edit Expert Advisor Review
agent_scope_database.content: A future iteration of the Launch Agent 6 Artifact will specify guidelines for obtaining specialized review of proposals requiring advanced technical or financial analysis.

agent_scope_database.name: Root Edit Proposal Review By Operational Facilitator
agent_scope_database.content: Within seven (7) days of the proposal being submitted, the Operational Facilitator must review the Root Edit Proposal for alignment. If the proposal is aligned, the Operational Facilitator must respond to the Forum post to announce their finding. In this Forum post, the Operational Facilitator must also confirm that the proposal is feasible for Operational GovOps to operationalize. If the proposal is misaligned, the Operational Facilitator must respond to the Forum post to announce their finding and provide the reasoning for it.

agent_scope_database.name: Root Edit Token Holder Vote
agent_scope_database.content: Where their review of the proposal results in a finding of alignment with the Sky Core Atlas and Launch Agent 6 Artifact, the Operational Facilitator next triggers a Snapshot poll to allow token holders to vote on the proposal. The poll is open for three (3) days. A poll must have at least 10% of the circulating token supply participating and must have 50% of votes in favor to be approved.

agent_scope_database.name: Root Edit Artifact Update
agent_scope_database.content: At the conclusion of the poll, if the proposal is approved, the Operational Facilitator submits the edit to Powerhouse to formally update the Agent Artifact. Regardless of the outcome, the Operational Facilitator updates the Powerhouse System to include the result of the vote, including any pertinent documents.
